org.transitime.db.structs

Class Match

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.transitime.db.structs.Match
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    @Immutable
@Entity
public class Match
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    For persisting the match for the vehicle. This data is later used for determining expected travel times. The key/IDs for the table are vehicleId and the AVL avlTime so that the Match data can easily be joined with AvlReport data to get additional information.

    Serializable since Hibernate requires such.

    Author:
    SkiBu Smith

      • isAtStop

        public boolean isAtStop()
        Returns true if vehicle is at or near a stop. The atStop member is transient which means it is not set properly if the Match object was read from the database. It is only set when the Match is created by the predictor software.
